{\large \textbf{\begin{tcolorbox}\textsc{Key Projects}\end{tcolorbox}}}
\begin{itemize}
\item \textbf{Short term Traffic Prediction Using DTC} \hfill\hfill(\textit{Mar'17- Ongoing})\\\textbf{Mentor: }\textbf{Prof. Ketan Rajawat}, Department of Electrical Engineering.
\begin{itemize}
\item Implemented matrix completion via rank minimization using the \textbf{SVT (Singular Value Threshold)} algorithm.
\item Successfully implemented the \textbf{Dynamic Tensor Completion(DTC)} algorithm. It was designed in such a way so as to utilize the multimode information to forecast traffic data while maintaining the low rank constraint.
\item Collected Traffic data from PeMS and structured it into a 4-D tensor.Ran DTC on this tensor to obtain the MAE(Mean Absolute Error) close to 10. Our Future intent is to design a fast online algorithm for predicting Real time Traffic data.
\end{itemize}
\item \textbf{TV Denoising of Signals with Poisson Distribution}\hfill\hfill(\textit{May'17-Ongoing})\\\textbf{Mentor: }\textbf{Prof. Ivan Selesnick}, Department of Electrical Engineering, New York University.
\begin{itemize}
\item Learned and worked on problems related to \textbf{Sparse regularization} and \textbf{Total variation(TV)}.
\item Analyzed the differences b/w the Poisson noise and
the Gaussian noise. Determined the problems with the Poisson noise like the dependence of variance on the input signal, presence of log(x) in the fidelity term etc.
\item Implemented the total variation Denoising (TVD) algorithm for Poisson noise using alternating direction method of multipliers (ADMM). Our target is to propose a non-convex penalty(more sparse than $l_1$ norm) for the objective function.
\end{itemize}
\item \textbf{Development Intern, RTE internship, IIT Kanpur} \hfill\hfill(\textit{May'17- July'17})\\%\textbf{Mentor: }\textbf{Prof. Manindra Agrawal}, Department of Computer and Science Engineering.
\vspace{-4mm}
\begin{itemize}[label={*}]
\item \textbf{Improve Phabricator-Jenkins integration} : Show summary of compiler errors in the Jenkins comment on Phabricator. 
 \item \textbf{Fix automatic version bump setup} : Bump the version number automatically . Depending on the command ,it will bump the Major/ Minor/Patch accordingly before publishing the app.
\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}
